   "correctedAnswer": "A current asset is an asset that is expected to be converted into cash or used up within one year or within the company's normal operating cycle, whichever is longer. A non-current asset, on the other hand, is an asset that is not expected to be converted into cash or used up within one year or within the company's normal operating cycle."
